V and optical continua at gas\ntemperatures $T \\gtrsim 12,000$ K over the deep chromosphere with log$_{10}$\ncolumn mass /[g cm$^{-2}$] of $-1.2$ to $-2.3$. These models explain the color\ntemperatures and Balmer jump strengths in high-cadence M dwarf flare\nobservations, and they clarify the relation among atmospheric, radiation, and\noptical color temperatures in stellar flares.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 9 Jan 2023 16:10:12 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 4 Feb 2023 00:52:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-07"}
