 point as function of the average density\n$n$, for finite values of $\\langle N \\rangle$ are finite and relatively small,\nin contrast to the results of the traditional calculations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 9 Jan 2023 17:58:14 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 14 Feb 2023 17:13:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-01"}
