 studies are performed which illustrate ice sheet\nproblem regimes for which the Gauss-Newton data-misfit Hessian is more\nefficiently approximated by the HODLR matrix format than the low-rank (LR)\nformat. We then demonstrate that HODLR approximations can be favorable, when\ncompared to global low-rank approximations, for large-scale problems by\nstudying the data-misfit Hessian associated to inverse problems governed by the\nStokes flow model on the Humboldt glacier and Greenland ice sheets.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 9 Jan 2023 19:30:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-11"}
