15$-$17$ and $22$-$24$ ISMBHs through astrometric\nmicrolensing, with the relative errors for all physical parameters less than\n$1,~5,~10\\%$, respectively. Microlensing events owing to ISMBHs with a mass\n$\\simeq 10$-$25 M_{\\odot}$ and located close to the observer with $D_l \\lesssim\n0.5 D_s$ while the source is inside the Galactic disk can be characterized with\nleast errors.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 10 Jan 2023 06:48:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-22"}
